'''Ars''' Latin word meaning Art(s). This is a noun, and in Latin has declensions, which are changes in the word corresponding to its use. One variation is "Artis," as in [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer|MGM]]'s slogan, ''Ars Gratia Artis'' (Art for art's sake). Other examples in common use:

   Ars Magica - The art of magic, or the magical arts.
   Ars Technica - Technical arts.
   Ars Poetica - The art of poetry.

   Ars longa, vita brevis. Art is long, life is short.